        <p class="metadata">Posted by Thomas Weidner (thomas) on 2008-12-17T00:09:31.000+0000</p> 
        <div class="body">
            <p>As the error describes you are calling the size validator like this:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
Zend_Validate_File_Size(10, 30);
</code></pre>

<p>and this is depreciated since 1.7.0 or 1.6.2.
As described in the manual you should use</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
Zend_Validate_File_Size(array('min' =&gt; 10, 'max' =&gt; 30));
</code></pre>

<p>This is not a failure but the only way to inform users that their input is not correct.</p>

        </div>
